An approximation to the consumption function could be constructed by linear interpolation between the {m,
~ ~c} points. But a vastly more accurate approximation can
be made (for a given number of gridpoints) if the interpolation is constructed so that
it also matches the marginal propensity to consume at the gridpoints. Differentiating
(105) with respect to a (and dropping policy function arguments for simplicity) yields a
marginal propensity to have consumed ca at each gridpoint:
