J Relational Diagrams for the Inequality Conditions
J.1 For the Unconstrained Perfect Foresight Model
Figure J.1 should be read as follows. The three nodes represent the values of the
absolute patience factor Þ, the growth factor for permanent income Γ, and the riskfree
interest factor R. The arrows between these quantities represent imposition of the labeled
condition. For example, the uppermost arrow, pointing from Þ to Γ, reflects imposition
of the PF-GIC condition. To make interpretation of the diagram easy, the mathematical
representation of the condition is expressed in parentheses as being equivalent (≡) to
the condition.
The imposition of the negation of the PF-GIC (the lower curved arrow pointing from Γ
